  <div class="post-body">
    <p>"Don't let your learning lead to knowledge, you'll become a fool. Let your learning lead to action, you can become wealthy."</p>
    <p>
      A Jim Rohn clip I keep replaying to remind myself:
      <a
        href="https://youtu.be/Eb3KznMqYu4"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >Discipline</a
      >. Knowing the right thing is worthless until I actually act on it.
    </p>
    <hr class="post-divider" />
    <p>
      His point: start with the <em>little</em> disciplines. Get excited
      about the small things you can already do and knock them out, both for
      the results and for the muscle. They are the reps that get you ready
      for the big challenges later. Skip the small ones and you'll never be
      able to handle the big ones.
    </p>
  </div>
